<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Illegal-Seek on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/illegal-seek/</link><description>Recent content in Illegal-Seek on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/illegal-seek/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C errno 29 ESPIPE — Illegal seek</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-29/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-29/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-errno-29-espipe--illegal-seek"&gt;[Solution] C errno 29 ESPIPE — Illegal seek&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Illegal seek occurs when a system call fails and sets &lt;code&gt;errno&lt;/code&gt; to 29. This error indicates that the requested operation cannot be performed due to the specific condition described by ESPIPE.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling lseek() on a pipe, socket, or FIFO.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trying to rewind a non-seekable file descriptor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using fseek() on a stream connected to a pipe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attempting to set file position on a device that doesn&amp;rsquo;t support seeking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;unistd.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;errno.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;string.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; pipefd[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;pipe&lt;/span&gt;(pipefd);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;off_t&lt;/span&gt; pos &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;lseek&lt;/span&gt;(pipefd[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;], &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;, SEEK_SET);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (pos &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fprintf&lt;/span&gt;(stderr, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;lseek failed: %s (errno %d)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;strerror&lt;/span&gt;(errno), errno);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;close&lt;/span&gt;(pipefd[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;]);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;close&lt;/span&gt;(pipefd[&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;]);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;sys/stat.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;errno.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; stat st;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fstat&lt;/span&gt;(STDIN_FILENO, &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;st) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;S_ISFIFO&lt;/span&gt;(st.st_mode)) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;printf&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Standard input is a pipe/FIFO - lseek will fail&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-29/"&gt;errno-29 ESPIPE&lt;/a&gt; — illegal seek (self).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-13/"&gt;errno-13 EACCES&lt;/a&gt; — permission denied.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-32/"&gt;errno-32 EPIPE&lt;/a&gt; — broken pipe.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C errno ESPIPE — Illegal seek Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-espipe/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-espipe/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-errno-espipe--illegal-seek-fix"&gt;[Solution] C errno ESPIPE — Illegal seek Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When &lt;code&gt;lseek()&lt;/code&gt; is called on a file descriptor that does not support seeking — such as a pipe, socket, FIFO, or certain device files — the call fails and sets &lt;code&gt;errno&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;ESPIPE&lt;/code&gt;. These file descriptors are sequential streams and have no concept of a file offset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling &lt;code&gt;lseek()&lt;/code&gt; on a pipe created with &lt;code&gt;pipe()&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling &lt;code&gt;lseek()&lt;/code&gt; on a socket file descriptor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling &lt;code&gt;lseek()&lt;/code&gt; on a FIFO (named pipe).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calling &lt;code&gt;lseek()&lt;/code&gt; on &lt;code&gt;/dev/null&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;/dev/zero&lt;/code&gt;, or other special devices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Check the file type before calling &lt;code&gt;lseek()&lt;/code&gt;. Use &lt;code&gt;fstat()&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;isatty()&lt;/code&gt; to determine if seeking is supported.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>